sentences: Timo Andres (born Timothy Andres in 1985 in Palo Alto, California) is an American composer and pianist.
Andres first rose to prominence at the age of 24 when his piece Nightjar was commissioned and performed by the Los Angeles Philharmonic and John Adams.
2010 – "Shy and Mighty" (Nonesuch) with David Kaplan, piano
2013 – "Home Stretch" (Nonesuch) with Metropolis Ensemble and Andrew Cyr
2019 – "Work Songs" (New Amsterdam) with Becca Stevens, Gabriel Kahane, Ted Hearne, Nathan Koci, and Taylor Levine
